              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "> Monkey business that worked </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Mailchimp was initially a side project within a web design agency called The Rocket Science Group. For years, it quietly served a niche group of clients who needed simple email advertising tools. However, they realized that the side project was growing faster and attracting more interest than their core design business. They quickly shut down their <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-26-07-2025-design-business-to-go-all-in-on-mailchimp" target="_blank">design business to go all-in on Mailchimp</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/mass-mailing-newsletter-templates-ab-testing-analytics.jpg" alt="The mass-mailing service provides excellent templates for creating newsletters for distribution lists and offers advanced options, including A/B testing and analytics" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>The mass-mailing service provides excellent templates for creating newsletters for distribution lists and provides advanced options, including A/B testing and analytics. Credits: Mailchimp</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Originally, it was a simple email newsletter tool designed to help small businesses communicate with their customers. Over time, it evolved into a comprehensive campaign platform, featuring a CRM, landing pages, social media scheduling, and e-commerce integrations. With AI tools like Growth Assistant, journey automation, upgraded SMS campaigns, and Canva integration, it has become an innovative, all-in-one platform. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          They offered the famous freemium pricing strategy, offering essential features. The Monkey Rewards referral program encouraged word-of-mouth, and on peak days, Mailchimp was acquiring 14,000 users every day. Mailchimp was eventually acquired by Intuit for $12B in 2021 in one of the largest tech acquisitions for a bootstrapped company. </p>
        </mj-text>
